Your `getSomething` is not returning anything. This translates to a [`204 No Content`](https://httpstatuses.com/204) response: The operation was successful (the `2xx` of the code indicates this) but there is nothing to return.

If you want to return something, change the return type from `void` to [`Response`](https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/ws/rs/core/Response.html).


    @POST
    @Path(&quot;/something&quot;)
    @Consumes(&quot;application/x-www-form-urlencoded&quot;)
    @Produces(&quot;text/plain&quot;)
    public Response getSomething() {
      return Response.ok(&quot;Success!&quot;).build();
    }

This will return the HTTP status code [`200 OK`](https://httpstatuses.com/200) with `Success!` as the content of the response body.

But you probably want to somehow *use* the content of the request. Take a look at https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4234084/jax-rs-retrieve-form-parameters for how you can do this.

