It is happening because of this property `android:layout_alignParentBottom=&quot;true&quot;`. This aligns the view to the bottom of your parent which is `RelativeLayout`. Since the height of `RelativeLayout` is `match_parent` it fills the whole screen and put your `ListView` at bottom.

1. Remove the property `android:layout_alignParentBottom=&quot;true&quot;` from your `ListView`. You might also want to remove `android:layout_centerVertical=&quot;true&quot;`.

2. Make your`ListView` to be below the `selected_item_textview` using `layout_below` property.

3. You can adjust the margins as required.

```
 &lt;ListView
        android:id=&quot;@+id/lvw&quot;
        android:layout_width=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
        android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
        android:layout_alignParentStart=&quot;true&quot;
        android:layout_below=&quot;@id/selected_item_textview&quot;
        android:layout_marginStart=&quot;-1dp&quot;
        android:layout_marginBottom=&quot;-9dp&quot; /&gt;
```

