I had the same issue in Android Studio (java files), both with data from hardcoded text and with data from users fields.

Changing

    BaseFont fontName = BaseFont.createFont(&quot;assets/fonts/verdana.otf&quot;,&quot;UTF-8&quot;,BaseFont.EMBEDDED);

to

    BaseFont fontName = BaseFont.createFont(&quot;assets/fonts/verdana.otf&quot;,&quot;ISO-8859-1&quot;,BaseFont.EMBEDDED);

did the trick.

If it worked for you when reading info from outside than the problem you are experiencing is most likely your environment encoding. I.e. your strings are not read as UTF-8 or any other encoding that supports your characters. So, I would suggest to convert your `String rawString = &quot;&#228;&#246;&#252;&#223;1234&#39;&quot;;` into Unicode sequence to check that your string indeed properly encoded.
You can try this code:

    String testStr1 = &quot;&#228;&#246;&#252;&#223;1234&#39;&quot;;
    String encoded1 = StringUnicodeEncoderDecoder.encodeStringToUnicodeSequence(testStr1);
    String restored = StringUnicodeEncoderDecoder.decodeUnicodeSequenceToString(encoded1);
    System.out.println(testStr1 + &quot;\n&quot; + encoded1 + &quot;\n&quot; + restored);
The result should be:

    &#228;&#246;&#252;&#223;1234&#39;
    \u00e4\u00f6\u00fc\u00df\u0031\u0032\u0033\u0034\u0027
    &#228;&#246;&#252;&#223;1234&#39;

If it is not, you have incorrect default charset for your environment. But also as a workaround you can send the String  `\u00e4\u00f6\u00fc\u00df\u0031\u0032\u0033\u0034\u0027` instead of `&#228;&#246;&#252;&#223;1234&#39;` and that should work. The class `StringUnicodeEncoderDecoder` is a good tool for testing thorny encoded issues, I used it very effectively many times. It comes with an Open Source MgntUtils library written and maintained by me. Here is a [Javadoc for the StringUnicodeEncoderDecoder class][1]. The library can be obtained as a Maven artifact from [Maven Central][2] or from [GitHub][3] (with source code and Javadoc)


  [1]: https://michaelgantman.github.io/Mgnt/docs/com/mgnt/utils/StringUnicodeEncoderDecoder.html
  [2]: https://search.maven.org/artifact/com.github.michaelgantman/MgntUtils
  [3]: https://github.com/michaelgantman/Mgnt/releases

