**Preface:**

This warning occurs if you are using not the same version in JavaFX dependencies, installed JDK and or compile version of your project. 

Why is this warning important? Your fxml document is allowed to use features from JFX 21, but your SDK is just JFX 17. 

This means, that your compiled application may have bugs because it maybe uses JFX 21 features, but it does not support them, because it uses JFX 17. And you will not notice that during development. :(

**Solution 1:** 

Tell your fxml file to use JFX 17! To do that, open your fxml file and change the needed information in the root tag:

Take a look at the attribute `xmlns=&quot;http://javafx.com/javafx/17&quot;`. The number &quot;17&quot; is the supported JavaFX version. There can be &quot;21&quot; for example too. In your case, put 17 there.

    &lt;BorderPane xmlns=&quot;http://javafx.com/javafx/17&quot;
                xmlns:fx=&quot;http://javafx.com/fxml/1&quot;
                fx:controller=&quot;com.wedasoft.project.views.main.MainViewController&quot;&gt;
         ...
    &lt;/BorderPane&gt;

**Solution 2:** 

Change the compile verion of your JavaFX dependencies to 21. To do that, take a look in your build.gradle / pom.xml file and change the version.

Example for build.gradle: 

    ext {
        javaFxVersion = &#39;17.0.8&#39;
    }
    javafx {
        version = &quot;${javaFxVersion}&quot;
        modules = [&#39;javafx.controls&#39;, &#39;javafx.fxml&#39;]
    }


Example for pom.xml: 

    &lt;dependencies&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.openjfx&lt;/groupId&gt;
